! `math` widget — examples

!! Arithmetic

| Expression | Result |h
| `1 + 2 * 3` | <$math>1 + 2 * 3</$math> |
| `√144` (√ unicode) | <$math>√144</$math> |
| `∛27` (∛ unicode) | <$math>∛27</$math> |
| `2² + 3²` (superscripts) | <$math>2² + 3²</$math> |
| `½ + ¼` (vulgar fractions) | <$math>½ + ¼</$math> |
| `π * 2` (π unicode) | <$math>π * 2</$math> |
| `τ / 2` (τ = 2π) | <$math>τ / 2</$math> |

!! Decimal separator

NNBSP (U+202F, narrow no-break space) is always used as thousands separator per ISO 80000-1.
Only the decimal separator varies.  Scientific exponents render as Unicode superscripts.

| Expression | `decimal="point"` (default) | `decimal="comma"` |h
| `123456.789` (''`notation="fixed"`'') | <$math notation="fixed">123456.789</$math> | <$math notation="fixed" decimal="comma">123456.789</$math> |
| `123456.789` (''`notation="scientific"`'') | <$math notation="scientific">123456.789</$math> | <$math notation="scientific" decimal="comma">123456.789</$math> |

!! Notation modes

| Expression | `notation="auto"` (default) | `notation="fixed"` | `notation="scientific"` |h
| `1234` | <$math notation="auto">1234</$math> | <$math notation="fixed">1234</$math> | <$math notation="scientific">1234</$math> |
| `12345` | <$math notation="auto">12345</$math> <br> (over 10³ → scientific) | <$math notation="fixed">12345</$math> |  <$math notation="scientific">12345</$math> |
| `0.001234` | <$math notation="auto">0.001234</$math> | <$math notation="fixed">0.001234</$math> | <$math notation="scientific">0.001234</$math> |
| `0.00012345` | <$math notation="auto">0.00012345</$math> <br> (below 10⁻³ → scientific) | <$math notation="fixed">0.00012345</$math> | <$math notation="scientific">0.00012345</$math> |
| Expression | `notation="engineering"` | | |h
| `12345` | <$math notation="engineering">12345</$math> ||
| Expression | `notation="bin"` | `notation="oct"` | `notation="hex"` |h
| `42` | <$math notation="bin">42</$math> | <$math notation="oct">42</$math> | <$math notation="hex">42</$math> |

⚠️ bin/oct/hex: `decimal` and `precision` are ignored. Non-integer values are truncated silently (`3.7` → `3`). Negative values are accepted.

!! Formula rendering

`show="formula"` and `show="full"` render the expression typeset — via KaTeX by default, as pretty-printed plain text with `output="text"`.

| Expression | `show="result"` (default) | `show="formula"` | `show="full"` |h
| `sqrt(x^2 + 1)` (''`scope={x:2}`'') | <$math scope="{x:2}">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$math> | <$math scope="{x:2}" show="formula">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$math> | <$math scope="{x:2}" show="full">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$math> |
| `(a+b)/c` (''`scope={a:1,b:2,c:3}`'') | <$math scope="{a:1,b:2,c:3}">(a+b)/c</$math> | <$math scope="{a:1,b:2,c:3}" show="formula">(a+b)/c</$math> | <$math scope="{a:1,b:2,c:3}" show="full">(a+b)/c</$math> |
| `pi * r^2` (''`scope={r:2}`'') | <$math scope="{r:2}">pi * r^2</$math> | <$math scope="{r:2}" show="formula">pi * r^2</$math> | <$math scope="{r:2}" show="full">pi * r^2</$math> |
| `factorial(5)` | <$math>factorial(5)</$math> | <$math show="formula">factorial(5)</$math> | <$math show="full">factorial(5)</$math> |
| `log10(1000)` | <$math>log10(1000)</$math> | <$math show="formula">log10(1000)</$math> | <$math show="full">log10(1000)</$math> |

Block display (`mode="block"` — works for both `output="katex"` and `output="text"`):

<$math show="full" mode="block">sqrt(3^2 + 4^2)</$math>

<$math output="text" show="full" mode="block">sqrt(3^2 + 4^2)</$math>

!! `output="text"` — plain text mode

Numbers in formulas use NNBSP (U+202F) as thousands separator.  Scientific exponents use Unicode superscripts.

| Expression | `output="text"` `show="formula"` | `output="text"` `show="full"` |h
| `pi * 1000000` | <$math output="text" show="formula">pi * 1000000</$math> | <$math output="text" show="full">pi * 1000000</$math> |
| `sqrt(x^2 + 1)` | <$math output="text" show="formula">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$math> | <$math output="text" show="full">sqrt(9 + 1)</$math> |
| `42` (plain literal — formula/full → result) | <$math output="text" show="formula">42</$math> | <$math output="text" show="full">42</$math> |

