!! Variables via scope tiddler

''Prerequisite:'' create a tiddler titled `MyVars` with this content:

```
r: 5
h: 10
density: 2.7
```

Then:

| Expression | Result |h
| `π * r^2` (circle area) | <$math scope="MyVars">π * r^2</$math> |
| `π * r^2 * h` (cylinder volume) | <$math scope="MyVars">π * r^2 * h</$math> |
| `density * π * r^2 * h` (mass) | <$math scope="MyVars">density * π * r^2 * h</$math> |

!! Variables via inline scope

| Expression | Result |h
| `pi * r^2 * h` | <$math scope="{r: 3, h: 10}">pi * r^2 * h</$math> |
| `sqrt(a^2 + b^2)` | <$math scope="{a: 1.5, b: 2.5}">sqrt(a^2 + b^2)</$math> |

!! BigNumber precision

| Expression | `calcPrec="float"` | `calcPrec="64"` |h
| `1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13` | <$math>1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13</$math> | <$math calcPrec="64">1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13</$math> |
| `0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1` | <$math>0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1</$math> | <$math calcPrec="64">0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1</$math> |

!! Error messages & debouncing

The widget waits 200 ms after the last change before showing an error. Examples:

| Expression | Message |h
| `sqrt(` | <$math>sqrt(</$math> |
| `1 / 0` | <$math>1 / 0</$math> |
| `sqt(4)` | <$math>sqt(4)</$math> |
| `1 +` | <$math>1 +</$math> |
| `not_a_function(1)` (silence → blank) | <$math silence="yes">not_a_function(1)</$math> |
